                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-87-off453 t18220703-87-crimeloc456"></join>. On the 14th of June, my hat was in the kitchen at night: the prisoner had lodged in the house for six weeks; he only had one hat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220703-87-person770">
                  JOHN 
                  HASKIN
               <interp inst="t18220703-87-person770" type="surname" value="HASKIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-87-person770" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-87-person770" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. About four o'clock in the morning, I saw the prisoner come out of the house with a bundle; I stopped him and found this hat in the bundle; he had his own on; he said this was his.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I bought a hat of a man at night, and in the morning took this by mistake.</p>
